Sentencas: The contact resistance and chemical compatibility of LaCo0.6Ni0.4O3-delta (LCN) coated Ni-Mo-Cr alloy are investigated at 750 degrees C in air for more than 530 h to simulate the contact situation of cathode/contact layer/interconnect in SOFC stacks.
Titulo: Chemical compatibility and electrical contact between Ni-Cr-Mo alloy and LaCo0.6Ni0.4O3-δ in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: With La0.72Sr0.18MnO3 (LSM) as the cathode, the area specific resistance (ASR) of LSM/LCN/Ni-Mo-Cr alloy assembly increases to a maximum of 240 m Omega cm(2) during the early stage of the test, and decreases after 55 h to a steady level of similar to 220 m Omega cm(2) till the end of the test.
Titulo: Chemical compatibility and electrical contact between Ni-Cr-Mo alloy and LaCo0.6Ni0.4O3-δ in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The contribution of formed oxide scale on the alloy to the measured ASR is negligible, compared to that of big AgLaMo2O8 particles sporadically distributed in LCN matrix.
Titulo: Chemical compatibility and electrical contact between Ni-Cr-Mo alloy and LaCo0.6Ni0.4O3-δ in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: AgLaMo2O8 is formed of evaporated Mo from the alloy, Ag from the testing lead and La from the LCN before the oxide scale on the alloy is well developed.
Titulo: Chemical compatibility and electrical contact between Ni-Cr-Mo alloy and LaCo0.6Ni0.4O3-δ in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This reaction is expected to cease once the oxide scale is fully established.
Titulo: Chemical compatibility and electrical contact between Ni-Cr-Mo alloy and LaCo0.6Ni0.4O3-δ in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
